<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-164-080 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 032 426</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Object-Oriented Programming  May 1991 v4 n2 p32(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A visual programming environment for building Smalltalk-80 views.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jiang, Zhihe; Bourne, John R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The ViewBuilder visual programming tool supports interactivedesign and automatic interpretation of Smalltalk-80 views andtheir attendant controllers.andP;  ViewBuilder can be used to buildviews interactively by specifying the types, locations and layoutsof views in a visual programming environment.andP;  Prototypicalconstructs are used for the typicalmodel-view-controller-implemented views found in Smalltalk-80.andO;The three components of Smalltalk-80 views are the model, view andcontroller: the model is an object representing data structuresused in an application; the view is an object that determines howthe data in the model is displayed; and the controller is anobject that provides the protocol for interfacing the user withthe view and model.andP;  The process of designing amodel-view-controller in the Smalltalk environment is described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   ViewBuilder (Program development software) (Usage)Smalltalk-80 (Program development software) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Object-Oriented ProgrammingProgram Development TechniquesProgramming InstructionVisual ProgrammingInteractive SystemsSmalltalkProgram Development Software.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogram.andO;Caption:   A code fragment for the opening method of the code built for aview shown. (program)A code fragment for the selection-in-list built for Figure 2.andO;(program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>